<sample title="Textures">
	<sdk_desc>Updating mesh albedo texture using procedurally generated image data</sdk_desc>
	<desc>
		<brief>
			<para>This sample demonstrates how to create and update procedural textures on static meshes in real time using the C++ API.</para>
			<para>Each mesh is assigned a custom-generated image, which is updated every frame using a time-based color pattern. The pixel data is written manually into an <ui><link to="image_class">Image</link></ui> class instance, and the result is applied to the albedo texture slot of the mesh's material using <ui><link to="material_class" offset="setTextureImage_int_Image_int">Material::setTextureImage()</link></ui>.</para>
		</brief>
		<para>This method allows generating dynamic patterns, noise, or other procedural visuals without using compute shaders or external image files.</para>
	</desc>
	<tags>
		<tag>Render</tag>
		<tag>Procedural</tag>
	</tags>
</sample>